
# Architecture Overview

This project follows a layered architecture to keep the code organized, testable, and easy to extend.

## Layers

### Controller Layer
Exposes REST endpoints and handles HTTP requests and responses.

### Service Layer
Contains business logic, validation, and application rules.

### Repository Layer
Communicates with the database using Spring Data JPA.

### Model Layer
Contains domain entities such as `Book`.

## Current Domain Model

### Book
Fields:
- id  
- title  
- author  
- isbn  
- publishedYear  
- category  
- totalCopies  
- availableCopies  

## Database
The project uses PostgreSQL as the main database.  
Flyway is used for database migrations to ensure consistent schema evolution.

## Future Architecture Extensions
- User entity and authentication  
- Borrowing workflow  
- Search and filtering  
- Role-based access control  
